                <div class="hero-content">
                    <h1>The Apollo Missions</h1>
                    <p>Exploring the Moon and Beyond</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Introduction Section -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p>The Apollo program was a series of space missions conducted by NASA between 1961 and 1972. The primary goal was to land humans on the Moon and bring them back safely to Earth, which was successfully achieved by Apollo 11 in 1969. These missions are considered some of the most iconic and groundbreaking achievements in human history.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Apollo 11 Section with Image -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>Apollo 11: The Historic Moon Landing</h2>
                <div class="image-container">
                    <img src="30.jpg" alt="Apollo 11 Moon Landing" class="section-image">
                </div>
                <p>Apollo 11 was the first mission to land humans on the Moon. Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin made history on July 20, 1969. The famous words "That's one small step for man, one giant leap for mankind" marked this monumental achievement.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Apollo 13 Section with Image -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>Apollo 13: A Triumph of Ingenuity</h2>
                <div class="image-container">
                    <img src="31.jpg" alt="Apollo 13 Mission" class="section-image">
                </div>
                <p>Apollo 13 was intended to be the third crewed mission to land on the Moon. However, an oxygen tank explosion forced the crew to abort the mission. Despite this, the team displayed remarkable ingenuity to bring them safely back to Earth.</p>
            </div>

            <!-- Conclusion Section -->
            <div class="content-section">
                <h2>Legacy of the Apollo Program</h2>
                <p>The Apollo program paved the way for future space exploration and left a lasting legacy. The scientific data and samples returned from the Moon continue to inform space research, and the program's success inspired future generations of scientists, engineers, and astronauts. The Apollo missions represent humanity's determination and ability to achieve the extraordinary.</p>
            </div>

